  "executiveSummary": {
    "overview": "AbbVie.com is an AEM 6.5 Cloud-based corporate site with 321 pages across 14 templates. The site uses a component library of 21 AEM Core Components with extensive class-based variant modifiers. The signature design pattern is a top-left-only border-radius on image containers and content wrappers, which varies by viewport (64px desktop, 32px mobile). The site requires 24 EDS blocks covering 67 total variations to achieve pixel-perfect parity.",
    "keyFindings": [
      "21 distinct AEM component types found across all pages",
      "3 radius tokens (default=24px, medium=40px, large=64px) applied to all container-type blocks",
      "Responsive radius: desktop uses full values, mobile reduces by ~50%",
      "The AEM 'teaser' is the most polymorphic component — maps to 4+ different EDS blocks",
      "9 separator height variants (1px to 144px) used as layout spacers between sections",
      "6 theme variants (dark, light, medium, + stroke variants) modify any block",
      "The homepage hero has a carousel (Splide.js) with 3 patient slides — NOT a static image hero",
      "Brightcove video player used on 2/5 template types (Science, Story)"
    ],
    "totalBlocksRequired": 24,
    "totalVariationsRequired": 67,
    "totalTemplatesRequired": 14,
    "migrationReadiness": "75% — Storybook covers 19/24 required blocks but needs 5 new components and 23 missing variations"
  },

